What you need to know:  The race, which started at Nyayo National Stadium, will see athletes cover 33 kilometres on the Nairobi Expressway and the remaining nine kilometres on other city roads before returning to NyayoA huge entry of 20 athletes from Ethiopia have signed for the men and women's marathonThe men’s and women’s winner will each pocket $60,000 (Sh6.9m) in prize money with the second-placed athletes in each of the categories going home $35,000 (Sh4.02m) richer